    <stitle>AFC 99904 - Frame Tie Bracket Replacement on 9900 Models</stitle>
    <afc id="afc99904">
        <afcnum>99904</afcnum>
        <afcdate>November, 1999</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>FRAME</subjectfile>
        <subject>Frame Tie Bracket Replacement on 9900 Models</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9900
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>07/01/1998</startdate>
                        <enddate>05/03/1999</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>It has been determined that the frame tie brackets on 9900 Models built between July 1, 1998 to
                    May 3, 1999 may show signs of fatigue at approximately 150,000 miles. If one or both frame tie
                    brackets fail and are not replaced, progressive frame damage could occur. An improved frame tie
                    bracket has been developed and is in production for 9900 Models. This improved frame tie bracket can
                    be retrofitted to 9900 Models built between July 1, 1998 to May 3, 1999.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
