        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="1">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Park the vehicle on a flat, level surface and chock the wheels to prevent property damage
                        and/or personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Batteries expel explosive gases. Keep sparks, flames, burning cigarettes or other ignition
                        sources away at all times. Always wear safety glasses and a face shield when working near
                        batteries to prevent personal injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9990401">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9990401" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g9990401.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="300"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the crossmember located between the frame tie brackets.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery cable and the ECM ground wire from the negative battery
                    terminal.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the battery box with a floor jack or suitable means of support.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all but one bolt from the battery box mounting bracket and left tie rod
                    bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the battery box mounting bracket and left frame tie bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the right frame tie bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the battery box bracket, new improved frame tie brackets and re-install the
                    crossmember following the previous steps in reverse order.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the frame tie bracket fasteners to 120 ft-lbs. (163 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the crossmember fasteners to 240 ft-lbs. (325 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the support from the battery box.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the battery cable and the ECM ground wire to the negative battery terminal.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
